OL,7,FFrank Dillon, defending, told the
OL,8,Fcourt: "The younger accomplice was the
OL,9,Fprincipal offender. They set off from
OL,10,Fhis house and they returned to his
OL,11,Fhouse. There are no grounds for
OL,12,Finferring that this defendant was the
OL,13,Fringleader.
OL,15,F"The defendant's lack of previous
OL,16,Fconvictions is a mitigating factor.
OL,17,FThis stain will be something which he
OL,18,Fwill bear for the rest of his days.
OL,19,FFamily members speak of the many good
OL,20,Fqualities of this defendant.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/14
