OL,7,F"It may be that, in due course, he
OL,8,Fwill be apprehended and tried for this
OL,9,Fserious offence.
OL,11,F"The jury rejected your account that
OL,12,Fyou were merely a shocked bystander
OL,13,Fand found that you participated in
OL,14,Fthis planned and vicious attack.
OL,16,F"For some inexplicable reason, you
OL,17,Fplanned to confront individuals from
OL,18,Fwhat you regarded as a rival area. You
OL,19,Fspotted the boy and his friends on
